# Voice-bot / Asterisk Conventions

Applies to Asterisk PBX, WebRTC, SIP, RTP, and coturn configuration.

## Context

- Full architecture and host topology: `VOICE-BOT-HANDOFF.md`, `CONTAINERS.md`.
- WebRTC setup sequence and fixes: `asterisk/docs/asterisk-webrtc/` (numbered runbooks).

## Rules

- Treat the numbered runbooks in `asterisk/docs/asterisk-webrtc/` as the source of truth;
  when changing config, update the matching runbook/checklist.
- For WebRTC endpoint changes, verify against `asterisk/docs/asterisk-webrtc/08-checklist.md`
  and the 488 / one-way-audio diagnostics before declaring done.
- RTP/ICE/coturn changes must keep the Docker networking constraints in mind
  (see `03-rtp-ice-docker.md`, `05-coturn.md`).
- Never commit real SIP credentials; rotate immediately if leaked (see `17-rotate-*`).
- After dialplan or pjsip edits, run `asterisk/scripts/test-voice-bot-asterisk.ps1`.
